22:46.031 --> 22:56.486
You see it, I've approached a couple of you this week and I've talked to you about becoming involved in the life of the church.

22:58.128 --> 22:59.410
But what about the rest of you?

22:59.938 --> 23:02.100
Just, hey, you know what, brother, hey, sister?

23:02.781 --> 23:04.123
I see you doing this.

23:04.203 --> 23:12.993
Have you thought about talking to pastor, talking to the divisional leaders about the gifting that you have and getting plugged in somewhere?

23:14.935 --> 23:18.859
Why do you think some members might hesitate to use their gifts?

23:21.922 --> 23:22.964
Help us as a body.

23:24.085 --> 23:27.308
Be part of the body and help us talk through those.

23:27.389 --> 23:28.690
Come up with answers.

23:30.114 --> 23:31.095
I'm not an expert.

23:32.237 --> 23:34.099
I'm just, this is what I do for a living.

23:34.860 --> 23:38.344
So I have answers, but I'll tell you right now, I don't have all the answers.

23:38.625 --> 23:39.346
It's not possible.

23:41.228 --> 23:41.949
I'm not the father.

23:44.312 --> 23:45.614
But help us think through.

23:45.654 --> 23:50.319
Again, as a quote from Rayner in his book, I'm the church member.

23:50.580 --> 23:55.506
He says, with a country club membership, you pay others to do the work for you.

23:56.002 --> 23:59.346
with church membership, everyone has a role or a function.

23:59.686 --> 24:03.170
We are all different, but we are necessary parts of the whole.

24:04.712 --> 24:13.161
So there used to be a mindset in the old days, I'm not gonna tell you how far back that was, because for some of us it was always still alive.

24:13.181 --> 24:21.490
But in the old days, there was a mindset within the church that the preacher, the pastor, whatever you wanna call him, was the hired hand.

24:22.434 --> 24:33.828
And his job was to kind of do whatever it was the church wanted in particular the board, wanted him to do and he just served as really a labor.

24:34.549 --> 24:40.116
He was the hired voice and the board was in control.

24:41.437 --> 24:46.944
Now I'm thankful that we have finally moved away from that because we don't see that as the biblical model.

24:50.348 --> 24:52.050
But there was this mindset that

24:52.962 --> 25:03.537
People would come to church, they would pay their, it's a T word, their tithes, except their mindset was, this was our membership dues.

25:04.379 --> 25:06.386
I pay my dues every week.

25:06.722 --> 25:08.945
And I expect the pastor to come and visit me.

25:09.005 --> 25:10.748
I expect the pastor to call me.

25:10.768 --> 25:17.237
If he doesn't call me, I'm gonna be mad because I need my, I wanna sing the songs in church that I like.

25:17.498 --> 25:21.543
I don't wanna sing those new songs or those old songs, whichever the case may be.

25:21.824 --> 25:27.392
I wanna be able to sit on my row because my family has been in this church for X number of years.

25:27.652 --> 25:29.094
And this is my family's row.

25:29.134 --> 25:30.536
We've always sat there.

25:30.556 --> 25:34.482
We pay our dues to make that happen.

25:36.706 --> 25:58.170
versus being a church member where everybody has a function and we bring our surplus, our tithe into the storehouse so that the church has the resources to continue to do the ministry that God has called us to do in this body at this time.

26:00.753 --> 26:05.458
And so here's what I want to encourage us to do is I want us to embrace our differences

26:05.858 --> 26:07.681
and work together for the glory of God.

26:08.182 --> 26:23.410
Listen, in this room, watching online, there are people of varying religious backgrounds, some of you came from Catholicism, some of you came from Lutheranism, some of you may have come from different, what we would consider pagan or cult.

26:23.586 --> 26:24.728
backgrounds.

26:25.630 --> 26:28.455
Some of you have come from no faith background.

26:28.475 --> 26:30.399
There are people of varying skin colors.

26:30.700 --> 26:33.805
There are people of varying cultural aspects.

26:34.206 --> 26:46.770
Even those, and again, I realize I'm saying something you already know, but even those within the same country, whether it's us here in the U.S., and I'm from California, and Sister Letitia's from what we would consider the South, or

26:46.914 --> 26:53.603
Those of you that are from Africa and you're from different African nations and have different cultural backgrounds, it doesn't matter.

26:55.125 --> 26:57.008
But we embrace who we are together.

26:57.929 --> 27:12.649
We embrace what we are as the body of Christ that somewhere, somehow, we all fit into the body that is laying out here at Compton and Russell ready to be raised up so that God can use us as a whole.

27:15.273 --> 27:15.954
Number three.

27:16.962 --> 27:22.948
Membership means everything we say and do is based on a biblical foundation of love.

27:24.970 --> 27:30.556
Many of us, of course, are familiar with the first Corinthians chapter 13, the love chapter.

27:30.576 --> 27:37.403
And everybody likes to quote it at Valentine's Day and at different anniversaries and things like that.

27:39.545 --> 27:44.530
These verses are often read kind of out of context.

27:46.114 --> 27:51.303
they're actually about how we should use our spiritual gifts within the church.

27:52.505 --> 28:02.100
Paul writes these words to a church that's experiencing conflict over spiritual gifts, and he emphasized that love is the foundation of using our gifts.

28:02.120 --> 28:03.984
1 Corinthians 13, verse one.

28:05.005 --> 28:10.354
So this is the predicate, the foundation of the rest of

28:10.722 --> 28:12.164
all the other list.

28:12.204 --> 28:22.775
He says, if I could speak all the languages of earth and of angels, but didn't love others, I would only be a noisy gong or a clanging symbol.

28:25.298 --> 28:26.379
Everyone knows somebody like that.

28:27.400 --> 28:32.226
Man, they just seemed to know everything, but you just didn't like being around them.

28:32.847 --> 28:38.453
Because it was just like, clang, clang, clang, clang, clang, clang, clang, clang.

28:38.473 --> 28:39.634
I love you, but I gotta go.

28:43.074 --> 28:53.187
If we don't love people, if we don't use our giftings, because we love those around us.

28:53.528 --> 29:01.318
So again, we're gonna talk a lot about the body at the corner of Compton and Russell.

29:01.338 --> 29:10.770
If this body stands up, if this body finds health and stands up and becomes a voice in the middle of this neighborhood,

29:11.714 --> 29:12.916
And we're not doing it.

29:12.996 --> 29:28.821
We've done it through too many medical shows, being on life support or having a tube down our throat or whatever it is, some artificial life-giving, life-keeping function.

29:30.984 --> 29:32.647
And we're not doing it out of love.

29:34.229 --> 29:35.391
Guess what our neighbors are going to hear?

29:36.913 --> 29:38.636
Clang, clang, clang, clang, clang.

29:38.656 --> 29:39.858
Because it's not going to match.

29:42.658 --> 29:59.987
What we do, how we act outside the four walls of this church are a better representation of who Christ is in you and ultimately in this body than just this functional building or anything like that.

30:03.473 --> 30:08.882
Without love, without loving people, our gifts are meaningless.

30:11.074 --> 30:26.780
How many of us, please don't raise your hands because I really, this is a rhetorical question, but how many of us would be willing to walk out those doors, walk down to the end of the block, walk up about, I don't know, eight, nine, 10 blocks and grab one of the folks sitting on the corner by the bus stop.

30:29.925 --> 30:32.089
Give him a big old hug and say, you know what, I am so sorry.

30:33.632 --> 30:35.154
The Lord loves you and he sees you.

30:35.874 --> 30:40.841
And I am so sorry that the world has treated you this way or that situations have caused you to be here.

30:41.262 --> 30:42.323
But here's what I want you to know.

30:42.384 --> 30:44.426
I want you to know that there's a Jesus who loves you.

30:44.747 --> 30:52.819
And if you will turn your eyes towards him, if you will serve him, I know that he will find an answer for the situation you're going through.

30:55.543 --> 30:56.224
I don't know.

30:56.444 --> 30:57.866
It's a rhetorical question.

30:58.787 --> 31:00.530
You have to answer that within your own heart.

31:01.314 --> 31:06.020
Love has to be the foundation of everything that happens within this church.

31:08.884 --> 31:10.006
Both good and hard.

31:11.368 --> 31:17.676
When good things are happening, it's easy to smile and joy and greet each other with love.

31:17.696 --> 31:21.682
Oh, brother or sister, God is good all the time.

31:23.424 --> 31:27.189
But when things are difficult or we're hitting a difficult patch and they're going to come and go.

31:29.733 --> 31:30.834
Being able to stop.

31:32.290 --> 31:38.116
and know that when we speak to each other through difficult situations, it's done in love.

31:40.218 --> 31:50.268
If I have to come to you as a pastor and tell you something that you don't particularly like, here's what I can tell you, there's not a person in this room or watching online that I don't love.

31:51.890 --> 32:00.338
Listen, we may not see eye to eye, we may not always agree, we may not always find unity in what we're saying, but the fact that I am

32:01.090 --> 32:02.572
your pastor and I do love you.

32:04.715 --> 32:07.539
Hopefully the same is reciprocated back.

32:08.581 --> 32:13.408
And when you tell me something difficult, I have to remind myself, they're coming from a place of love.

32:13.668 --> 32:17.774
I need to hear what they're saying and try to figure out where the breakdown is.

32:19.476 --> 32:26.386
And if we can come to an agreement, if we can find that foundation that everything that we do is done in love,

32:28.354 --> 32:29.776
It's going to help us move forward.

32:29.816 --> 32:33.180
It's going to help us get that body back up even that much faster.

32:34.301 --> 32:40.208
It was love that caused Jesus to step on to the planet and to rescue us from our sin.

32:40.688 --> 32:43.051
I'm not going to share it, but you know, John 3 16.

32:44.953 --> 32:50.280
He reminded us that it will be love that distinguishes the church from the world.

32:50.320 --> 32:52.402
If you look at John 13 35,

32:53.506 --> 32:58.871
says your love for one another will prove the world to the world that you are to my disciples.

33:01.414 --> 33:02.295
Do we do that?

33:03.556 --> 33:08.321
Do we, we're a temple international church?

33:08.341 --> 33:09.382
It's a rhetorical question.

33:10.523 --> 33:12.165
Do we do that?

33:12.765 --> 33:21.234
Do the people that we come in contact know that we are disciples of the Almighty because of how we love them?

33:26.146 --> 33:31.614
Rainer has this quote, he says, we are not to love fellow church members just because they are lovable.

33:31.874 --> 33:34.057
We are to love the unlovable as well.

33:34.117 --> 33:39.264
We are to pray for and encourage our pastors even when they do things we don't like.

33:39.625 --> 33:43.790
We are to serve the church even if we are alone in doing so.

33:46.975 --> 33:49.198
So as we close out this part of two more questions.

33:50.720 --> 33:53.143
Do you love the church and the people in it?

33:53.945 --> 33:55.026
Does that love

33:55.458 --> 33:58.282
Drive you to serve, give, and pray.

33:59.584 --> 34:01.927
If not, can you really call it love?

34:05.912 --> 34:10.298
If not, I might add that maybe this isn't the place for you.

34:13.523 --> 34:16.587
Because what we do and how we do it has to be done in love.

34:18.169 --> 34:18.930
Our last point.

34:19.682 --> 34:22.045
church membership is functioning church membership.

34:22.085 --> 34:32.360
This is the point of this particular message is that to be a member of a country club, you just pay your dues, but biblical church membership is different.

34:32.640 --> 34:38.889
Rainer writes, this is our last quote, do you know how to remain a biblical member of a church?

34:39.610 --> 34:42.514
Give abundantly and serve without hesitation.

34:42.754 --> 34:52.747
You can be a member of a church and not do this, but you cannot be a biblical member of the church without giving abundantly and serving without hesitation.

34:53.188 --> 34:58.555
Imagine with me if every member of our church gave abundantly and served without hesitation.

34:59.015 --> 35:00.958
What would it take for that to happen?

35:03.201 --> 35:04.663
Rainer has one final statement.

35:05.624 --> 35:10.290
Says, the concept of an inactive church member is an oxymoron.

35:12.418 --> 35:16.785
The concept of an inactive church member is an oxymoron.

35:18.247 --> 35:24.176
So I want you to ask yourself again a rhetorical question, how can I best serve my church?

35:24.196 --> 35:32.709
Better yet, are you willing to write the Lord a blank check and allow him to fill it out and to serve and to give whatever he writes?

35:35.593 --> 35:41.682
Rainer closes each chapter of the book that we're kind of loosely basing our information on.

35:42.786 --> 35:44.229
He ends it with a pledge.

35:44.931 --> 35:46.073
This is what the pledge says.

35:46.153 --> 35:47.937
It says, I am a church member.

35:48.118 --> 35:50.162
I like the metaphor of membership.

35:50.182 --> 35:53.630
It's not membership as in a civic organization or a country club.

35:53.890 --> 35:57.999
It is the kind of membership given to us in 1 Corinthians 12.

35:58.500 --> 36:02.930
It says, now you are the body of Christ and individual members of it.

36:03.202 --> 36:10.552
Because I'm a member of the body of Christ, I must be a functioning member, whether I'm an I, an ear, or a hand.

36:10.992 --> 36:19.243
As a functioning member, I will give, I will serve, I will minister, I will evangelize, I will study, I will seek to be a blessing to others.

36:19.604 --> 36:27.133
I will remember what 1 Corinthians 1226 states that if one member suffers, all the members suffer with it.

36:27.154 --> 36:30.578
If one member is honored, all the members rejoice with it.

36:31.490 --> 36:34.700
I want you to note though something as we're starting to wrap up.

36:34.720 --> 36:40.337
Note that there's no pledge to a pastor, there's no pledge to a board or a leadership team.

36:40.357 --> 36:43.506
This is a pledge as a member of the body.

36:43.586 --> 36:44.247
of Christ.

36:44.548 --> 36:47.332
It doesn't matter about the walls or the roof over us.

36:47.572 --> 36:49.255
It doesn't matter who stands up here.

36:49.576 --> 36:51.438
It doesn't matter what teams you're on.

36:51.659 --> 36:59.091
We're talking about giving a pledge, making a commitment to be a member of the body of Christ.

36:59.111 --> 37:00.313
So here's what I'm gonna ask you to do.

37:00.393 --> 37:01.414
I know it's kind of silly.

37:03.137 --> 37:08.025
But if you're willing to be a functioning church member, would you repeat this with me?

37:09.307 --> 37:11.250
Pledge should be there for us to look at.

37:14.946 --> 37:18.410
So if you're willing to say this with me, I'm just gonna read it and you can read it with me if you will.

37:19.211 --> 37:20.593
It says, I am a church member.

37:21.354 --> 37:22.915
I like the metaphor of membership.

37:22.955 --> 37:26.700
It's not a membership as in a civic organization or a country club.

37:27.300 --> 37:30.765
It is the kind of membership given to us in 1 Corinthians chapter 12.

37:31.245 --> 37:34.569
Now you are the body of Christ and individual members of it.

37:35.090 --> 37:38.674
Because I'm a member of the body of Christ, I must be a functioning member.

37:39.054 --> 37:42.258
Whether I'm an eye, an ear, or a hand.

37:42.530 --> 37:48.819
As a functioning member, I will give, I will serve, I will minister, I will evangelize, I will study.

37:49.180 --> 37:51.243
I will seek to be a blessing to others.

37:51.643 --> 37:58.734
I will remember that 1 Corinthians 1226 states, if one member suffers, all the members suffer with it.

37:59.154 --> 38:03.340
If one member is honored, all the members rejoice with it.

38:05.844 --> 38:07.186
So here's what we're going to do in closing.

38:08.066 --> 38:23.579
Being a functioning church member means recognizing that we're all necessary parts of the whole, we're all working together despite our differences, we're all operating from a foundation of love, and we're all committing to give and serve without hesitation.

38:24.921 --> 38:29.010
So want us to strive to be this kind of church member.

38:29.506 --> 38:38.297
the kind who build up the body of Christ, the kind who love and serve one another, and the kind who make a difference in our church and in our community.

38:40.440 --> 38:44.105
We're going to do something a bit different as we close out our time together today.

38:45.727 --> 38:50.313
And we're gonna respond to what we've heard in a bit different way than what we do traditionally.

38:51.174 --> 38:54.578
Today, we're going to come together as a church body.

38:54.850 --> 39:06.524
and we're gonna celebrate our differences and our uniquenesses and our unity in Christ by sharing around the Lord's table, remembering our Savior's sacrifice for all of us.

39:09.107 --> 39:14.654
Now, of course, if you need prayer or you need to respond to Jesus, the altars are always open for that.

39:17.658 --> 39:22.143
But as our ushers take their place and get ready to serve, I want us to pray.

39:22.203 --> 39:24.466
Let's bow our heads.

39:26.018 --> 39:28.781
Father, we thank you for making us part of the body of Christ.

39:29.743 --> 39:37.652
Help us to be functioning members who serve, who give, and love as you have called us to.

39:39.435 --> 39:43.360
Help us to find unity as the body of Christ.

39:45.803 --> 39:50.929
We pray these things over this congregation, both here in person and those watching online.

39:51.730 --> 39:54.994
It's in the name of Jesus we pray, amen.

